beer.beer_description:
C'mon Santa! Take a shower and cool off. Always complaining about dirty chimneys, gluten free cookies, cheeky reindeer and naughty children. But you're no saint. Your recent efforts to outsource present delivery to parents around the world has been noticed and is not okay! You have been naughty, but will you be nice?

Our biggest West Coast IPA to date, with huge kettle and dry additions of our favourite oldskool hops - Simcoe, chinook, Centennial and Columbus. We've even added a touch of fresh Pine Needle, Courtesy of North Coast Christmas Trees, to boost that special Xmas feeling.  Dank and Piney just like Santa's suit after a mischievous world tour.

Unwrap the holiday spirit with King Tide Brewing's NAUGHTY or NICE - Mid West IPA, our exclusive limited release Xmas beer. This festive brew boasts a perfect balance of hop-forward bitterness and malty sweetness, creating a delightful experience whether you've been naughty or nice.  Grab yours while it lasts and add a touch of cheer to your holiday festivities.

Made with NSW grown Voyager Malt and a combo of Aussie and US hops. The XPA delivers smooth tropical vibes and a full citrus flavour. Roll out your beach towel, crack out the cans and enjoy the view.

Come On, take the jump!

Brace yourself for a thrill as you plunge into the malt flavour and splash in the hoppy fun. Not just a dare, it's your Rite of Passage.

The road less travelled leads you through secluded bush, to pristine waters that await your discovery.
Wade in and embrace the haze from the cascading falls and enjoy the smooth and creamy body with juicy new world hops.

This is your hideaway.

An adventurous
IPA to celebrate an epic local bike track.

Hops: Centennial, Chinook, Simcoe
Malts: Pale, Munich,
Chocolate, Crystal
Yeast: American Ale

GABS2024 Festival Beer - Caramel sundae meets affogato meets imperial stout in this homage to a classic tune about a fashionable con-man. Lashings of dulce de leche, lactose and steaming Hope Road espresso transform this rich imperial stout into a deceptively smooth and crafty, late-night treat for the nightbirds. This is our second coffee beer collab with local espresso bar, Hope Road. We are two likeminded businesses in the Coffs Habrour CBD, with a passion for serving the local community with great drinks, good humour and fun times.

Looking to be one our or King Tide staples, is the new addition of the Blue Groper, Coffs’ original beer!

Born in the 80’s to quench the thirst of our great town, it started as the simple and honest idea of an enterprising local (Paul Amos) and grew into the Blue Groper, where he gave Coffs' it's very own beer! We have worked with Paul on reinventing and bringing back to life the Groper – an honest, beloved lager. Raise a Groper to Coffs Harbour!
A better beer. A better place.

beer.beer_name: Louie In the Sky With Terpenes
beer.beer_description: The intoxicating aromas of beech smoked malt, combine with mind bending flavours of strata hops and a little toke of something special – King Louie XIII cannabis terpenes.
With blueberry

If you like your house hard and your bass beefy, you need some Doof Doof in your life. A well structured malt profile, measured bitterness and a calculated layering of modern German hops that would make even the most disciplined German engineer loosen their lederhosen and dance on a table top.

Experience the rich, creamy texture of our SOUTH ISLAND STOUT - NITRO 4.0%, an Irish stout on nitrogen that perfectly balances roasted malt flavours with a smooth finish. Ideal for those who appreciate the traditional flavours of an Irish stout, this brew promises a delightful drinking experience with every sip.

Are your summer holidays plans torn between the warm golden beaches of Coffs Harbour or the crisp white sands of Jervis Bay? Well now you don't have to choose! Jervis Bay Brewing and King Tide Brewing have teamed up to bring you a hazy IPA, packed full of tropical hop goodness to cure your FOMO and help you float away on a dreamy holiday cloud. Harbour or Bay? Try both we'd say.

C'mon Santa! Take a shower and cool off. Always complaining about dirty chimneys, gluten free cookies, cheeky reindeer and naughty children. But you're no saint. Your recent efforts to outsource present delivery to parents around the world has been noticed and is not okay! You have been naughty, but will you be nice?

Our biggest West Coast IPA to date, with huge kettle and dry additions of our favourite oldskool hops - Simcoe, chinook, Centennial and Columbus. We've even added a touch of fresh Pine Needle, Courtesy of North Coast Christmas Trees, to boost that special Xmas feeling.  Dank and Piney just like Santa's suit after a mischievous world tour.

Full of flavour and bursting with 
excitement. A rite of passage, just
like its namesake. Take the Jump, if you dare!

Grab a mat and bolt up the stairs. The anticipation builds - do you ease into the mellow blue slide, with its open top and cruisy corners? or do you throw yourself head-first down the yellow tube of terror and race to an exciting end? The thrilling decisions of our youth. Ready yourself for a Coffs' classic. 
 
Cold IPA - pills and maize malt, US hops, fermented with lager yeast at ale temps. Expect lager-esque, boldly hopped and dry flavours. 
 
The iconic Aquajet no longer towers over Coffs Harbour. But the memory remains. Cheers to a simpler time. Splish Splash Splosh!
Pre-game, half-time or in the sheds, a true grandstander never stops pleasing the crowd. Brewed for refreshment and athletic good looks.
A German classic, made in the traditional style with 60% wheat malt and a distinctive yeast strain that brings big banana and clove flavours. Welcome to the Banana Republic. Welcome to Coffs!

Celebrate with King Tide Brewing's finest creation, the ANNIVERSARY ALE - BARLEYWINE. Specially crafted to honor our 3rd birthday, this rich, robust barley wine represents our commitment to quality and tradition. As King Tide's first foray into Barleywine, it delivers a unique, full-bodied flavour that’s perfect for commemorating special occasions.  Join us in toasting to three years of exceptional brewing with each unforgettable sip.
This Black IPA unites layers of roasted malts with Simcoe, Chinook, and Vic Secret hops for a flavour that leaves its mark - justice served with the letter Z.

Hope Road & King Tide Brewing share a common mission - to brew great drinks with gratitude, love and for the enjoyment of our local community. This collaboration pairs Hope Roads legendary espresso blend with a European lager made with NSW barley. Brewed in the laneway of Coffs Harbour for everyone to enjoy.
